  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Solids | Auto-Layer</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">What is &apos;Auto-Layer&apos;?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text> automatically adds an <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Extrusion-Offset" styleclass="Parameter">Extrusion Offset</link> to all <text styleclass="Element">Extrusions</text>. It is intended that extrusions do not collide as the machine cycles.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Notes">Note: </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Before you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text> this command, you would usually do <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Solids-AutoProfiles" styleclass="T_Menu">Solids toolbar &gt; Auto-Profile (Mechanism)</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To see the <text styleclass="Interface">Solids</text>, do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Visibility toolbar &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Visibility-Show-Model-in-Mechanism" styleclass="T_Menu">Show Solids in Mechanism</link> to see &#160;<text styleclass="Interface">Solids</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="5" colcount="3" style="head-row-background-color:#ffffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td rowspan="2" style="width:30px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="text-align:right;"><image src="Icon-AutoLayer.png" scale="100.00%"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:76px; height:26px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="text-align:right;">Toolbar : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:middle;">
          <para styleclass="T_Menu">Solids toolbar &gt; Auto-Layer</para>
        </td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:76px; height:26px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="text-align:right;">Menu : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:middle;">
          <para styleclass="T_Menu">Add menu &gt; Mechanism sub-menu &gt; Solids sub-menu &gt; Auto-Layer </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2" style="width:122px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="text-align:right;">To Layer : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Click </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Solids toolbar &gt; Auto-Layer</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT">- or -</para>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Click </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add menu &gt; Mechanism sub-menu &gt; Solids sub-menu &gt; Auto-Layer</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2" style="width:122px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="text-align:right;">Result : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text> moves, along the <text styleclass="Interface">Z-axis,</text> each <text styleclass="Element">Extrusion</text> element by a different offset distance. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">After <text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text>, when you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Run menu &gt; Cycle</text>, <text styleclass="Element">Extrusions</text> should move over each other, and not move through each other.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">You can edit the <text styleclass="Parameter-Header">Extrusion-Offset</text> and <text styleclass="Parameter-Header">Part-Offset</text> of each <text styleclass="Element">Extrusion</text> with the <text styleclass="Element">Extrusion dialog-box</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
